text:
When Your Construction Crew Decides to Host a Fashion Show.

There’s never a dull moment in blue collar work - especially when your crew gets bored! This story of a construction fashion show gone wrong is exactly why the skilled trades are never just about the work—it’s about the characters behind it. Have you ever had to save a job at the last minute because of crew shenanigans? Tell us your most memorable worksite story in the comments below!

text: From Billion-Dollar Bridges to Dog Houses: The Unexpected Journey of a Builder. From the depths of the ocean floor to building custom dog houses - blue collar careers are full of incredible moments and surprising turns. Share in the comments below and join our movement celebrating skilled trades!

text:
When “I’ll Show You How” Goes Terribly Wrong

When you warn about broken equipment and the boss decides to “show you how it’s done”...only to lose a toe in the process. Sometimes the hardest safety lessons come at the highest price.

text:
When “Be Right Back” Turns Into 8 Months

That time my union worker vanished after being sent for a tool, then casually returned with the wrench 8 months later like nothing happened. Lost Freddy and his legendary pipe wrench. #BlueCollarStories #bluecollar
